	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>3d March 5620</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I received a message<lb/> per <persName>Sarah Joseph</persName> which makes me<lb/> think you misunderstood what<lb/> I wrote about <persName>Dr Dawson&#39;s</persName> book.<lb/>  She writes me you said you cannot<lb/> notice the book until you had<lb/> seen it.  I thought the<lb/> article already in the Occident<lb/> notice enough.  I requested her<lb/> to inform you that I was<lb/> writing a Review of it for<lb/> a medical journal here.  The<lb/> first part appeared in <date>Feby</date> and<lb/> I am now correcting the proof of the</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>last.  When it is printed off I<lb/> shall send you a copy of it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Did you not also<lb/> misunderstand about sending<lb/> the Occident to <persName>Dr D.</persName> I asked<lb/> you to send a copy &#40;extra&#41;<lb/> containing the notice of his work&#44;<lb/> &#38; you appear to have understood<lb/> that I asked you to continue sending him a copy.  <persName>Dr D.</persName> is<lb/> such a busy man&#44; and so<lb/> thoroughly devoted to science<lb/> that he has little or rather<lb/> no time for theology.  I never<lb/> knew a man who does as<lb/> much as he does&#44; and with<lb/> such readiness &#38; little effort.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your venture is getting<lb/> near its end.  Do you</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>intend to change its form.<lb/>  I believe that the old form<lb/> would be much preferred<lb/> none here like it as it is.<lb/>  Many have the monthly bound.<lb/>  The <hi rend="underline">other</hi> <sic>weeklys</sic> are never<lb/> preserved.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">How gets on the Board of Delegates.  What a <hi rend="underline">powerful</hi><lb/> reply to <persName>Einhorn</persName> appears<lb/> in the Messenger.  It would<lb/> read well in the Herald<lb/> on t&#39;other side <persName>Einhorns</persName> article.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I must close&#44; as the<lb/> party who has promised to<lb/> take a few lines for me<lb/> is about to start.  Vale.</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
				<p>Did you see</p>
				<p>notice of <persName>Dr R</persName></p>
				<p><persName>Chief Rabbi</persName> of</p>
				<p><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> in <persName>Frank Littles</persName> paper&#63;</p>
		</body>
